fields.description: The main category of the dataset. A dataset can have multiple themes. The set of skos:Concepts used to categorize the datasets are organized in a skos:ConceptScheme describing all the categories and their relations in the catalog.

fields.label: distribution

fields.description: A Web page that can be navigated to in a Web browser to gain access to the dataset, its distributions and/or additional information.
fields.label: landing page

fields.description: Could be any kind of URL that gives access to a distribution of the dataset. E.g. landing page, download, feed URL, SPARQL endpoint. Use when your catalog does not have information on which it is or when it is definitely not a download. The value is a URL. If the distribution(s) are accessible only through a landing page (i.e. direct download URLs are not known), then the landing page link should be duplicated as accessURL on a distribution.
fields.label: access URL

fields.description: This is a direct link to a downloadable file in a given format. E.g. CSV file or RDF file. The format is described by the distribution's dc:format and/or dcat:mediaType. The value is a URL.
fields.label: download URL

fields.description: The size of a distribution in bytes. The size in bytes can be approximated when the precise size is not known. The literal value of dcat:byteSize should by typed as xsd:decimal
fields.label: byte size

fields.description: This property SHOULD be used when the media type of the distribution is defined in IANA, otherwise dct:format MAY be used with different values.
fields.label: media type

fields.description: describes the quality of data e.g. precision. This should not be used to describe the data collection characteristics, other more specialized statistical properties can be used instead. This term has been deprecated
fields.label: data quality (Deprecated)

fields.description: links a dataset to a dictionary that helps interpreting the data. This term has been deprecated
fields.label: data dictionary (Deprecated)

fields.description: describes the level of granularity of data in a dataset. The granularity can be in time, place etc. This term has been deprecated
fields.label: granularity (Deprecated)

fields.description: the size of a distribution. This term has been deprecated
fields.label: size (Deprecated)

fields.description: describe size of resource in bytes. This term has been deprecated
fields.label: size in bytes (Deprecated)

fields.description: The relation between something and the point, or other geometrical thing in space, where it is. For example, the realtionship between a radio tower and a Point with a given lat and long. Or a relationship between a park and its outline as a closed arc of points, or a road and its location as a arc (a sequence of points). Clearly in practice there will be limit to the accuracy of any such statement, but one would expect an accuracy appropriate for the size of the object and uses such as mapping .
